page.title: 02Bus Service Through Mulben
page.content: The A95 from Keith to Mulben runs almost paraallel to the Rosarie Burn and the Burn of Mulben. The Railway Line runs close by and also parallel. We can tell that there has been a road there for a long time because there is an old Toll House on the road to Keith and off our map. There is a public bus service along this road. Buses take fifteen minutes to travel from Keith to Mulben. You can get a bus in Keith at 09.00, 12.15 or 15.35 hours. The times of buses from Mulben are 08.35, 10.35 and 13.45 hours, and you arrive in Keith fifteen minutes later. These services operate on school days During school holidays, buses run on Tuesdays and Fridays only. The morning bus does not run in holiday time.
